   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">This manual provides information about installation, operation
or maintenance for <ph platform="PxW" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Reality PxW</ph>
         <ph platform="WxW" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Reality WxW</ph>
         <ph platform="SDC" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Reality SDC</ph> systems.</p>
      <p platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/p ">In this manual “the system” refers
to the complete single, dual or redundant system, and “the
unit” refers to one of the units in a dual or redundant system.
Also “the cabinet” refers to the mechanical frame of
the system or unit.</p>
      <p platform="SDC" class="- topic/p ">In this manual “the system” refers
to the complete single or redundant system, and “the unit”
refers to one of the units in a redundant system. Also “the
cabinet” refers to the mechanical frame of the system or unit.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The customer specific documents <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Single Line Diagram</i>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Cross Reference List</i>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i>, and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Circuit Diagrams</i> are often referred to. Each system is engineered based on customer
specifications and requires that you are familiar with the exact configuration
of the system before installing, operating or performing maintenance
on the system.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Any breaker or switch mentioned in this manual can be a switch-disconnector,
fuse switch-disconnector or circuit breaker. Please see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Single
Line Diagram</i> for type used in your system.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The standard reference designators for parts are mentioned and
might be different.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">All images are only for illustration. The shown examples might
differ from the actual system.</p>
